message: Add vision feedback to ReferenceStripFeeder.
Disable this unfinished feature for now.
Quick note before patching dev.
Pulling changes back in after screwing up the merge.

Merging some standalone features and code from the job processor refactor:
Adds crop to camera base. Fixes #171.
Shows camera names in the All Cameras view. Makes it easier to identify what you are looking at. This is always on right now, might need to be an option if it bothers people.
Removed the dead bottom vision API from VisionProvider. This was no longer used now that the bottom vision system is complete.
Adds the ability to limit FPS in the OpenCvCamera. This is an easy way to decrease CPU load. I've found even 5 fps is more than enough.

Add camera crop #171
Add nozzle runout compensation #235

Change UiUtils to use invokeLater instead of invokeAndWait as this was causing problems with the new JobProcessor. There should be no noticible affects otherwise.
Removed Bottom Vision API from VisionProvider. See CHANGES.md for details.
Added FPS setting for OpenCvCamera, making it easier to reduce CPU load.
Added a feeature to show the name of each camea when in All Cameras view. See CHANGES.md for details.
Finished up the new job planner. Seems to be working well but needs some real world testing.
Fixed several of the remaining issues in JobPanel related to the JobProcessor refactor. Skip is now functioning correctly and several previous errors are handled better.

Reorganized a lot of the job processor code.
Started work on the real planner.
Cleaned up option strings in job error dialog.

Adds auto transition to FSM.
ReferencePnpJobProcessor getting pretty close to finished. Only have planner left to do. Currently using a dummy planner.
JobPanel working but lots of edge cases not handled. Documented with STOPSHIP.
AbstractMachine.submit changed to clear the task queue before calling the callback, instead of after. This allows the callback to schedule tasks. Needs lots of testing.

This is all a huge mess, but it's slowly coming together. Next changes will be large, so checking this in as a checkpoint. Note, not checking in some changes to AbstractMachine that I am not committed to yet, and without those this doesn't work at all, so don't use this yet.

Add state listener for FSM.
Add null action handling to FSM.
Add retry count to feeder.

Merge branch 'develop' into feature/job-processor-refactor

  GcodeDriver now ignores blank lines in Gcodes.

  Update README.md
